I have a fairly simple function in C to convert a created PNG image (stored in memory) into a PDF file.

I was looking at speeding up my code, and noticed that for 17 x A4 pages, it took around 3 minutes 29 seconds to complete my code (it does other things in the background), when running LibHPDF v2.3.0 on a Raspberry Pi 3B+ (32 bit).

I compiled v2.4.5 of LibHaru from source and was surprised that the time to process the same document increased to 4 minutes 48 seconds.

Having reverted back to LibHPDF-dev, the time dropped back down to 3:29 minutes, so it is something in the library causing this.

Has anyone else noticed this - could it be the way the LibHPDF is packaged uses some compilation optimisations which are not in the standard make package?


